wikipedia_page.main: William Addis Fagan (15 December 1832 – 14 March 1890) was an Irish Liberal politician.He was elected as the Member of Parliament (MP) for Carlow Borough at the 1868 general election but stood down at the next general election, in 1874.At some point, Fagan was also Captain of the 12th Royal Lancers.
